    "created_at": "2019-04-09T14:30:49Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-04-09T14:30:49Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "BTW I tried to come up with minimal example that reproduces the issue but couldn't. It takes the full blown integration test of all our system to reproduce it. Luckily we have it and apparently it only requires to swap 2 lines - to start the hosting before spawning the new processes - for the issue to reproduce.\r\n\r\nBut there is one more problematic scenario caused by the handle leak that this fix resolves: we have a service listening on a well-known port that needs to recycle from time to time. If it has spawned a child process during its lifetime that is still up, then after recycling it won't be able to listen on the same port - the port is held open by the child process.\r\nThis one is dead-easy to reproduce."
